This repo is here to help you seting quickly a linux environement as 42 use.
The main goal is to set up your pc and then practice.
You can not find solution or code here.
Only example file of configuration and some intresting resource ;)

LINUX (Ubuntu/Debian):
#Update 
sudo apt get update && sudo apt get upgrade

# For gcc, gdb, valgrind and make
sudo apt install build-essential valgrind 
gcc --version && make --version && gdb --version && valgrind --version

# Install git
sudo apt install git 
git config --global user.name "Your name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@coffee.fr"
git --version

# Install Norminette (for 42 coding rules)
# Repo official: https://github.com/42school/norminette
# Take look at their pdf rules (~20 min)
sudo apt install python3-setuptools
sudo apt install pipx
pipx install norminette
pipx ensurepath
norminette --version

# Check Vim
Vim --version 

# If you want to know some basic use of vim (~20 min)
vimtutor

# vim header to automate it
# Repo official: https://github.com/42paris/42header 
# This cp command may not work, follow their repo guide :)
# Also check ~/.vimrc in this repo to see other vim config
cp stdheader.vim ~/.vim/plugin

# Additional utilities
sudo apt install man manpages-dev


You find this repo usefull then we some coffee <3
